{"id":101101,"name":"Basecamp Highlight Your Assigned ToDos","description":"The original Basecamp applied a yellow background to tasks that were assigned to you. This is missing from the Basecamp 2, and can make it hard to pick out your tasks if you have many long lists. This style applies the yellow background again, but requires a little digging in order to find your unique user ID used by Basecamp under the hood. You can also apply colors for other Basecamp users.","user":{"id":87333,"name":"beporter","email":"beporter2@gmail.com","paypal_email":"beporter@gmail.com","homepage":null,"about":"Just this guy, you know?","license":"ccbyncsa"},"updated":"2016-01-27T13:52:23.000Z","weekly_install_count":0,"total_install_count":208,"rating":null,"after_screenshot_name":"https://userstyles.org/style_screenshots/101101_after.png?r=1674201613","obsoleting_style_id":null,"obsoleting_style_name":null,"obsolete":0,"admin_delete_reason_id":null,"obsoletion_message":null,"screenshots":["https://userstyles.org/style_screenshots/101101_additional_10944.png?r=1674201613","https://userstyles.org/style_screenshots/101101_additional_10945.png?r=1674201613"],"license":null,"created":"2014-05-03T21:17:15.000Z","category":"site","raw_subcategory":"basecamp","subcategory":"basecamp","additional_info":"\u003cb\u003eSet Up\u003c/b\u003e\r\n\r\nThe following instructions assume you are using Chrome (instructions for other browsers or improvements to these welcome!):\r\n\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eRight-click on a ToDo task that has been assigned to you and choose \u003cb\u003e\"Inspect element\"\u003c/b\u003e. (This will open a panel at the bottom of your browser with the part of the HTML code you selected highlight.) (See the associated screenshot above for reference.)\r\n\u003cli\u003eMove up from the selected line one element at a time until you encounter the first \u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;li class=\"todo show\" ...\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e element.\r\n\u003cli\u003e Inside this tag will be a \u003ccode\u003edata-assignee-code=\"p1234567\"\u003c/code\u003e attribute. Make a note of the \"p\" number in quotes (including the 'p') as you'll need that to configure this style. (See the associated screenshot above for reference.)\r\n\u003cli\u003eNavigate to this styles homepage (if you're reading this, you're already here.)\r\n\u003cli\u003eEnter your \u003cb\u003epXXXXXXX\u003c/b\u003e number into the \u003ccode\u003edata-assignee-code\u003c/code\u003e box, and if you want, change the background color.\r\n\u003cli\u003eClick \u003cb\u003e+Install with Stylish\u003c/b\u003e.\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\r\nIf you participate in multiple projects owned by different accounts, you may need to repeat this process for each one. (That's why multiple \u003cb\u003edata-assignee-code\u003c/b\u003es are provided.) You could also use the extra codes to color other users' tasks differently.\r\n\r\n\u003cb\u003eChange Log\u003c/b\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e2016-01-27 - Added more \"spots\" for additional user codes. Updated readme.\r\n\u003cli\u003e2015-10-22 - Once again fixed selectors to include \"single ToDo\" pages.\r\n\u003cli\u003e2015-03-09 - Added a bit of padding to ToDos to assist readability of highlighted items a little.\r\n\u003cli\u003e2014-05-14 - Fixed CSS selectors for single ToDo list pages.\r\n\u003cli\u003e2014-05-03 - Initial creation. Added ability to control multiple highlighting colors for either multiple accounts, or different users. Added screenshots.\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e","style_tags":[],"css":"@-moz-document domain(\"basecamp.com\") {\r\nli.todo.show span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    padding-left: 4px;\r\n    padding-right: 4px;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    padding-left: 4px;\r\n    padding-right: 4px;\r\n    border-radius: 5px;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-1]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-1]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-2]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-2]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-3]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-3]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-4]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-4]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-5]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-5]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-6]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-6]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-7]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-7]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-8]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-8]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-9]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-9]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-10]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-10]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-11]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-11]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-12]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-12]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-13]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-14]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-14]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-14]]*/;\r\n}\r\nli[data-assignee-code=\"/*[[assignee-key-15]]*/\"] span.wrapper span.content {\r\n    background-color: /*[[highlight-color-15]]*/;\r\n}\r\n}\r\n","discussions":[],"discussionsCount":0,"commentsCount":0,"is